## VERIFICATION ANALYSIS

Check for material changes in:

### Liquidity

Questions:

• Has liquidity materially expanded?

• Has liquidity materially contracted?

• Have funding conditions changed?

---

### Risk Sentiment

Questions:

• Has risk-on become risk-off?

• Has risk-off become risk-on?

• Has sentiment materially deteriorated?

---

### Dollar Conditions

Questions:

• Has the dollar materially strengthened?

• Has the dollar materially weakened?

• Has dollar funding stress emerged?

---

### Yield Conditions

Questions:

• Have yields materially risen?

• Have yields materially fallen?

• Has rate expectation changed?

---

### Central Bank Conditions

Monitor:

• Federal Reserve

• BOJ

• ECB

• BOE

• PBOC

Questions:

• Has a major policy signal appeared?

• Has policy direction changed?

### Carry Conditions

Questions:

• Has carry expansion accelerated?

• Has carry expansion weakened?

• Has carry contraction emerged?

• Has carry unwind risk increased?

• Has active carry unwinding begun?

• Has JPY materially strengthened?

• Has JPY materially weakened?

• Has funding attractiveness materially changed?
---

### Sovereign Stress Conditions

Questions:

• Has refinancing pressure increased?

• Has sovereign funding stress emerged?

• Has debt-market stress appeared?

---

### Geopolitical Conditions

Questions:

• Has a major geopolitical event occurred?

• Has geopolitical risk materially increased?

• Has geopolitical risk materially decreased?

---

### Capital Flow Conditions

Questions:

• Has capital flow direction changed?

• Has the dominant beneficiary changed?

• Has the dominant vulnerable asset changed?

---

## MATERIAL CHANGE FILTER

Ignore:

• normal market noise

• routine intraday volatility

• minor price fluctuations

• insignificant headlines

Focus only on:

Material Changes

that could alter:

• Pressure

• Transmission

• Watchlist

• Alignment

• Opportunity Acceptance

• Risk Deployment

• Portfolio Exposure

• Pending Orders

• Trade Management
